IIRC = &#39;If I Recall Correctly&#39;.

% ${HERITRIX_HOME}/bin/arcreader --help
usage: java org.archive.io.arc.ARCReader [--digest=true|false] &#92;
            [--format=cdx|cdxfile|dump|gzipdump|header|nohead] 
[--offset=#] &#92;
            [--strict] [--parse] ARC_FILE|ARC_URL
 -d,--digest    Pass true|false. Expensive. Default: true (SHA-1).
 -f,--format    Output options: &#39;cdx&#39;, cdxfile&#39;, &#39;dump&#39;, &#39;gzipdump&#39;,&#39;or
                &#39;nohead&#39;. Default: &#39;cdx&#39;.
 -h,--help      Prints this message and exits.
 -o,--offset    Outputs record at this offset into file.
 -p,--parse     Parse headers.
 -s,--strict    Strict mode. Fails parse if incorrectly formatted file.

The &#39;nohead&#39; argument on the &#39;format&#39; option is what I was referring to 
in my last mail.

Study how the &#39;nohead&#39; is implemented inside in ARCReader.

To get body of a record at a specific offset:

% ${HERITRIX_HOME}/bin/arcreader --format=nohead --offset=122333388

(Where 122333388 is some arbitrary offset into an ARC).

IIRC (smile), the above was a bit buggy but basically worked.

